🔹 Project Description
VaxiPredict – Vaccine Hesitancy Intelligence Platform

VaxiPredict is a Streamlit‑based AI‑driven dashboard that predicts and analyzes vaccine hesitancy at the individual and community level. It combines GNN‑LSTM models with real‑world demographic, behavioral, and rumor‑propagation data to:

Identify high‑risk communities likely to resist vaccination

Visualize hesitancy trends over time and geography

Recommend targeted interventions (education, outreach, reminders)

Monitor the impact of campaigns and policy changes

Built entirely in Python, VaxiPredict is designed for public‑health teams, policymakers, and researchers who want an interactive, real‑time view of vaccine confidence—without writing code.

🔹 Key Features
Multi‑page Streamlit UI (Predictions, Interventions, Networks, Reminders, Rumours, Reports, Settings, Vaccines)

User‑friendly login / auth flow

Centralized predictive dashboard with metrics, charts, and filters

Network‑style visualization of rumor spread and community clusters

Reminder and rumor‑tracking modules to support public‑health outreach
